GERMAN giants Bayern Munich are weighing up a move for Super Eagles hitman Victor Osimhen as a replacement for wantaway Robert Lewandowski. Polish hitman Lewandowski has already stated his desire to leave German this summer, with Barcelona a likely destination. Due to this, German champions would be in the market this summer to search for a worthy replacement for the club’s second-highest goalscorer.   MARCELO: How Brazilian became Real Madrid legend     Ronaldo: ‘I don’t follow records, records…     Boxers battle for N1m at GOtv Boxing Night 25   Super Eagles striker Victor Osimhen had a brilliant campaign with Napoli last season, scoring 18 times in 31 appearances and helping his side to a third-place finish in the Serie A. The 23-year-old has been the subject of numerous transfer talks since January, with reports linking him with a move to the Premier League.